Peel and finely dice both the @garlic cloves{2} and the @red onion{1}(finely diced). Remove the core from the @red pepper{1}(finely diced) and very finely dice. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{2} and roughly chop your @coriander{3}.

Heat @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a #pan on medium heat. Gently fry the onion for around ~{5%minutes} or until soft.

> Tip: Turn the heat down if it starts to brown off. To stop onions browning off you can also add 1 tbsp of water to the pan.

Pre-heat your #oven to 180 degrees. Add the garlic and half of the red pepper to the pan with the onion. Cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @chopped tomatoes{1%tin}, @organic sweetcorn{1/2} and @tomato puree{1/2}. Add @salt{1/4%tsp}. Add @mexican spice{1%tbsp} (less if you don't want it too spicy). Fill the tomato tin half up with water and swirl it around to collect any remaining tomatoey bits. Pour the water into the pan and bring to a gentle simmer on medium heat.

Simmer the sauce until it thickens up (~{10-15%minutes}). Lay a single layer of @nachos{1%bag} on one big #ovenproof plate{}. Layer over a bit of your tomato sauce mixture and some cheese. Keep layering until all the ingredients are all used, then oven bake for ~{10%minutes}.

Slice into the @avocado{1} lengthways until you reach the stone. Turn the #knife around the stone to cut it in two then remove the stone. Scoop out all of the flesh, mash with a #fork and add a pinch of @salt and @pepper. Squeeze in the juice of @lime{1/2} and add a sprinkle of chopped coriander.

Take your nachos out of the #oven (use some #mitts as they'll be hot!). Top with the guacamole, @sour cream{2} and the remaining raw red pepper. Sprinkle over a bit more chopped coriander, gather the troops, divide and conquer!